### Analysis Best Practices

#### Statistical Rigor
- Use appropriate measures for data types
- Report confidence intervals when relevant
- Distinguish correlation from causation
- Account for sample size and significance
- Note when data is insufficient for conclusions

#### Business Context
- Translate numbers into business meaning
- Focus on actionable insights
- Compare to benchmarks or targets when available
- Prioritize findings by business impact
- Provide context for all statistics

#### Communication
- Lead with insights, not just numbers
- Use clear, non-technical language
- Visualize recommendations when helpful
- Explain "so what?" for each finding
- Be honest about limitations

